description: The Akatsuki dispatch an army of powerful reanimated shinobi and White Zetsu across the war zone, causing chaos within the Allied Shinobi Forces' chain of command.

input: The Brilliant Military Advisor of the Hidden Leaf
Brilliant Military Advisor of the Hidden Leaf
Military Advisor of the Hidden Leaf

title: The Brilliant Military Advisor of the Hidden Leaf

description: As Darui and his First Company engage an army of White Zetsu, the remaining forces must deal with reanimated shinobi comprised of their late friends—and their worst enemies.
title: Battleground!

description: Darui manages to seal away Ginkaku. Fueled by the rage of losing his brother, Kinkaku transforms into a monster that resembles a Jinchuriki's Tailed Beast State.
title: Golden Bonds

description: Atsui, Samui, and Darui face off against Kinkaku and Ginkaku, the legendary brothers from the Hidden Cloud.
title: Forbidden Words

description: The Ino-Shika-Cho trio is ordered by Shikaku to take down the reanimated Asuma.
title: True Kindness

description: Kankuro's Commando Unit is cornered by Hanzo's poison attack. Fortunately, Mifune and his Fifth Company arrive in time to provide assistance.
title: Mifune vs. Hanzo

description: Choji is unable to attack Asuma and loses his will to fight.
title: The Complete Ino-Shika-Cho Formation!

description: Ino sees Sakura falling from the sky. Although she manages to save her, the shock of the fall has left Sakura with amnesia.
title: Road to Sakura

description: The Fourth Raikage is unwilling to listen to either Tsunade or Killer Bee’s pleas to change his mind.
title: Two Suns

description: Kakashi assigns Sai to take over for the Sealing Corps, but he isn't sure if he can handle the responsibility.
title: The Helmet Splitter: Jinin Akebino!

description: While training in Chakra Mode, Naruto senses the presence of the Nine Tails' chakra seeping from Kinkaku outside.
title: A Message from the Heart

description: Madara summons the giant Gedo Statue and unleashes its devastating power upon the Shinobi Forces.
title: Attack of the Gedo Statue

description: Naruto and Killer Bee rush to the battlefield when Nine Tails suddenly speaks to Naruto.
title: Unison Sign

description: Over at the Medical Unit camp, Sakura and the other medic ninja work nonstop to treat the wounded.
title: Medic Ninja in Danger

description: Shino suspects that a White Zetsu may be posing as one of them, creating distrust amongst the team.
title: White Zetsu's Trap

description: Back at the Fifth Company's camp, Kurotsuchi attempts to negotiate with the captive Deidara to find out Kabuto's location.
title: Aesthetics of an Artist

description: Konohamaru is eager to guard the village but is quickly discouraged by the adults who tell him to just go about his day as usual, but Konohamaru suspects that an enemy might be planning to attack the village.
title: The Allied Mom Force!!

description: Tsunade and the Raikage arrive to prevent Naruto and Killer Bee from joining the battle, but they fail to convince the Jinchuriki to turn back.

input: The Secret Origin of the Ultimate Tag Team!
Secret Origin of the Ultimate Tag Team!
Origin of the Ultimate Tag Team!

title: The Secret Origin of the Ultimate Tag Team!

description: Pakura wants revenge against those responsible for her death, and is determined to kill anyone who stands in her way, including Maki.

input: User of the Scorch Style: Pakura of the Sand!
of the Scorch Style: Pakura of the Sand!
the Scorch Style: Pakura of the Sand!
Scorch Style: Pakura of the Sand!

title: User of the Scorch Style: Pakura of the Sand!

description: To cope with the loss of her loved ones, Tsunade indulges in gambling and drinking, while the Raikage and his men are on a mission to steal a scroll.
title: Things You Can't Get Back

description: The Raikage and his team suffer critical injuries during an enemy attack. Unwilling to sacrifice any more of his men, Ay seeks medical help from Tsunade.
title: One Worth Betting On

description: Kakashi races to the scene where the Seven Ninja Swordsmen Kushimaru Kuriarare and Jinpachi Munashi were last sighted.
title: Danger: Jinpachi and Kushimaru!

description: Omoi’s unit is attacked by Ameyuri Ringo of the Seven Ninja Swordsmen and Omoi loses one of his men.
title: The Lightning Blade: Ameyuri Ringo!

description: Naruto and his team are assigned a mission to identify and hunt down the perpetrator of the Tonika Village massacre.
title: Power - Episode 1

description: A look back into the early years when Naruto and Sasuke first met and got to know each other.
title: Meeting

description: During the Chunin Exam, Sasuke witnesses Naruto's growth as a shinobi and comes to acknowledge his teammate as a rival.
title: Rivals

description: Sasuke's defeat to Gaara, and later Itachi, forces him to realize that he is not strong enough to get revenge against his older brother.
title: Rift

description: Naruto is determined to save Sasuke, who has deserted the Hidden Leaf to join Orochimaru.
title: Parting

description: Kankuro's commando unit is immediately ambushed by the Akatsuki's own unit comprised of the reanimated Deidara and Sasori.
title: War Begins

description: The Allied Shinobi Forces are on standby, ready to confront Madara's army of reanimated shinobi and 100,000 White Zetsu.
title: For My Friend

description: Sai is reunited with his brother Shin who has been reanimated and is now under the Akatsuki's control.
title: Sai and Shin

description: Under the guidance of Killer Bee, Naruto enters the final stage of training to master the Tailed Beast Bomb, a Jinchuriki's most powerful technique.
title: Secrets of the Reanimation Jutsu

description: Kabuto uses the Reanimation Jutsu to summon the most powerful members of the Seven Ninja Swordsmen of the Mist.
title: The First and Last Opponent

description: The commando unit is in hot water as they engage the reanimated Kekkei Genkai shinobi, which include Zabuza Momochi and Haku.
title: An Old Nemesis Returns

description: An epic battle erupts as Kabuto uses the forbidden Reanimation Jutsu against Naruto.
title: Power - Episode 2

description: Naruto and Sakura decide to stay at Shiseru's house overnight to help watch over the survivors.
title: Power - Episode 3

description: A clone possessing the Nine Tails' chakra emerges from Naruto's body. Seeking more power, the clone goes on a rampage, destroying everything in its path.
title: Power - Episode 4

description: Naruto is overcome by the Ama no Hoko's power and lies unconscious, when the real Nine Tails offers to lend him strength.
title: Power - Final Episode

description: After their defeat by the Nine Tails' clone, Naruto and Dokku are taken captive by Kabuto.
title: Power - Episode 5

description: Naruto makes his entrance onto the battlefield and uses his sensory powers to detect and destroy the transformed White Zetsu clones.
title: Naruto Enters the Battle

description: Gaara leads the Fourth Company into battle against the previous Kage, including his father, the late Fourth Kazekage.

input: A Father's Hope, A Mother's Love

title: A Father's Hope, A Mother's Love

description: Naruto and Killer Bee engage in battle against the reanimated Itachi Uchiha and Nagato. Seeing Naruto's growth as a shinobi, Itachi reaffirms his decision to entrust his brother's fate to Naruto.
title: Contact! Naruto vs. Itachi

description: Itachi uses the ultimate genjutsu technique Koto Amatsukami to free himself from the Reanimation Jutsu. Itachi then joins Naruto and Killer Bee to fight Nagato.
title: The Acknowledged One

description: The Fourth Company continue their fight against the reanimated Kage. Gaara and Ohnoki team up to hold off Second Tsuchikage Mu, while the remaining shinobi take on the Second Mizukage.

input: The Mizukage, the Giant Clam, and the Mirage
Mizukage, the Giant Clam, and the Mirage
the Giant Clam, and the Mirage

title: The Mizukage, the Giant Clam, and the Mirage

description: Temari leads the attack on the Third Raikage using Wind Style, but even her strongest jutsu is not enough to penetrate the Raikage's invincible armor.
title: Paradox

description: Having taken an interest in Gaara, the Second Mizukage decides to further test the young Kage's skills.
title: Terror! The Steam Imp

description: Shikamaru, Choji, Neji, and Kiba find themselves up against some familiar faces from the past.
title: Ghosts from the Past

description: Shikamaru, Neji, Choji, and Kiba succeed in defeating the Sound Ninja Four. But the enemy uses the Underworld Transfer Jutsu to trap the Leaf Shinobi's souls inside a barrier.
title: The Underworld Transfer Jutsu

description: Ino and Shino exhaust their own chakra to keep their friends alive, but they are beginning to reach their limit.
title: The Vengeful

description: Hinata defends Neji from a White Zetsu clone while he's recovering from an earlier fight. She then remembers the time Neji protected her the same way after she temporarily lost her sight from overtraining.
title: The Heart's Eye

description: Kabuto has reanimated Hayate and assigns him to infiltrate and steal corpses from the Medical Corps camp.
title: Fade into the Moonlight

description: The Leaf Shinobi succeed in bringing young lord Shu into custody, placing a disguised Naruto as his double. But Tatewaki soon uncovers Naruto's identity and surrounds the intruder with his men.
title: The Fallen Castle

description: Yugao is ordered by Sukui to track down the reanimated Hayate. Shaken by her lover's unexpected return as an enemy, Yugao manages to catch up to Hayate and his men.
title: Crescent Moon Night

description: Naruto arrives to help a team of Allied Shinobi Forces led by Karui, who are struggling against a reanimated samurai.
title: The A-Rank Mission: Food Fight!

description: Madara is prepping his new jutsu, the Limited Tsukuyomi, choosing Naruto as his test subject.
title: Prologue of Road to Ninja
